From: Alan Stern <stern@rowland.harvard.edu>
Date: Thu, 21 Sep 2017 13:22:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] USB: g_mass_storage: Fix deadlock when driver is unbound
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.13.6
Git-commit: 1fbbb78f25d1291274f320462bf6908906f538db

commit 1fbbb78f25d1291274f320462bf6908906f538db upstream.

As a holdover from the old g_file_storage gadget, the g_mass_storage
legacy gadget driver attempts to unregister itself when its main
operating thread terminates (if it hasn't been unregistered already).
This is not strictly necessary; it was never more than an attempt to
have the gadget fail cleanly if something went wrong and the main
thread was killed.

However, now that the UDC core manages gadget drivers independently of
UDC drivers, this scheme doesn't work any more.  A simple test:

	modprobe dummy-hcd
	modprobe g-mass-storage file=...
	rmmod dummy-hcd

